President Trump held a meeting with members of the House and Senate leadership to discuss the September legislative agenda. The President thanked the leaders for their work and highlighted the progress that has been made in funding the government and addressing important issues such as military funding and the opioid crisis. He also emphasized the need to fund border security and support American law enforcement. The President mentioned ongoing negotiations with Canada on trade and expressed satisfaction with the progress made in the Middle East regarding Iran. He also mentioned the ongoing discussions with China on trade. In response to a question about Defense Secretary Mattis, the President praised Mattis and stated that he will stay in his position. The President also addressed a book written by journalist Bob Woodward, stating that he believes the book has been discredited. When asked about a potential government shutdown, the President stated that if it happens, it happens, but he is willing to do what is necessary to protect the country's borders.